      adjustment of $57,561 (1% x $5,756,125).
    </p>
    <hr class="mt-2 mb-6 border-gray-300">
    <h3>Vendor Costs</h3>
    <p>
      Vendor Costs are slightly different from Transaction Costs in that these
      costs are specific to you and would not necessarily be incurred by other
      buyers or sellers. For example, you may have a management contract with
      an early termination fee–an expense that is unique to your situation and
      not to the market as a whole.
    </p>
    <p>
      Vendor Costs are subtracted from the Net Reversionary Value to arrive at
      the Net Realizable Reversionary Value.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Net Realizable Reversionary Value is the amount of cash the vendor
      expects to receive from the sale after all costs (but before debt
      repayment), which is a key number for determining investment returns.
    </p>
    <p>
      ReturnSuite offers four options for Vendor Costs:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-8 text-gray-800 text-base pb-2 leading-8">
